Portland also announced it was re-signing second-year outside back Mo Mohamed. Like forward Walter Varela, Mohamed was initially released by the Hearts of Pine after the 2025 season but now is back on the roster. Mohamed was a midseason signing in 2025 and played in 17 games, making eight starts.

Portland now has eight defenders on its roster. Espinosa, Brecc Evans, Zion Scarlett and Serigne Mbacke Faye are new additions. USL League One All-League first-teamer Nathan Messer and center back Kemali Green are returning starters. Jaden Jones-Reilly also returns after missing most of the 2025 season because of an injury.

